00:01:49.811 --> 00:01:53.064
@croftandy asks:
"How much will it cost

00:01:53.064 --> 00:01:57.485
to preserve your virtual brain
on a future virtual grid?

00:01:57.485 --> 00:01:59.521
Will there be virtual jobs?"

00:01:59.521 --> 00:02:00.754
Well there are two questions there.

00:02:00.754 --> 00:02:03.290
Moving our brains
into the virtual world,

00:02:03.290 --> 00:02:06.993
kind of, confronts a series
of tough questions about biology,

00:02:06.993 --> 00:02:09.564
and about the way
the human brain is designed

00:02:09.696 --> 00:02:10.964
that are pretty challenging ones.

00:02:10.964 --> 00:02:13.034
I personally think
that we are going to see

00:02:13.034 --> 00:02:17.104
a very, very human AI's,
that are able to talk to us,

00:02:17.104 --> 00:02:20.174
and have intelligence
initially comparable to ours,

00:02:20.174 --> 00:02:21.209
and then, greater than ours,

00:02:21.209 --> 00:02:22.475
I think we were going to
see that happen

00:02:22.475 --> 00:02:25.379
a lot sooner, then we see
this ability to, sort of,

00:02:25.379 --> 00:02:28.916
upload yourself completely
into a virtual environment.

00:02:28.916 --> 00:02:30.584
I think it's a good question
for the future,

00:02:30.584 --> 00:02:32.620
but it's one that I don't know
how easy it's going to be to do,

00:02:32.620 --> 00:02:35.388
and I don't have as much confidence
that it will be straightforward

00:02:35.388 --> 00:02:37.959
as some of the other crazy things
that are happening right now.

00:02:37.959 --> 00:02:40.228
As for the question of virtual jobs,

00:02:40.228 --> 00:02:43.264
totally. There are already
many virtual jobs.

00:02:43.264 --> 00:02:46.500
So, the virtual world of second life
has somewhere between

00:02:46.500 --> 00:02:48.970
a half a billion
and a billion dollars a year

00:02:48.970 --> 00:02:51.839
in people buying and
selling things from each other,

00:02:51.839 --> 00:02:55.510
and many of those things are things
that are people's fulltime jobs.

00:02:55.510 --> 00:02:58.111
There are many, many people
in Second Life today,

00:02:58.111 --> 00:03:00.046
for example, who make
their real world living

00:03:00.681 --> 00:03:02.583
from building things
in the virtual world

00:03:02.583 --> 00:03:04.119
and selling them
to other people in there.

00:03:04.119 --> 00:03:06.988
So, virtual jobs are going to be
a dominant part of our future.

00:03:06.988 --> 00:03:10.624
I would go so far, as to say
there probably be

00:03:11.091 --> 00:03:13.493
the biggest place where we work,
bigger than the real world.

